## How to Comply

If you create further derivatives:
1. Keep both `LICENSE` (original) and `LICENSE.ADDITIONS` (this file)
2. Add copyright headers to files you modify:
   ```python
   # Copyright (C) 2024 funstory-ai Limited
   # Copyright (C) 2025 Miguel Enes — [previous modifications]
   # Copyright (C) [YEAR] [YOUR NAME] — [your modifications]
   # License: GNU Affero General Public License v3.0
   ```
3. Update `LICENSE.ADDITIONS` to document your changes
4. Link to the original BabelDOC project in your README
5. If you run this as a service, provide source code to users

